Appliances - Electricity Demand Calculation


objective: The submodule aims at modeling the electricity demand for the appliances over time.

main inputs: 
use of appliances by type in year x (appliance-use*[total hours per year]),
efficiency of appliances by type in year x (appliance-efficiency*[kWh/hour]),

main outputs: 
electricity demand (el-appliances[kWh/year])

Cost calculation

objective: Calculate Capex and opex.

main inputs: 
new appliances

main outputs: 
cost of new appliances

Total Energy Need per end-use
in residential and non-residential buildings


objective: 
The submodule aims at modeling the energy need per end-use in GWh by multiplying energy-needs/activity by activity data

main inputs: 
total residential floor area in year x (floor-space[m²]),
total non-residential floor area in year x (floor-space[m²]),
energy need per floor area for each building type in year x (energy-need_*[kWh/m2 year]), 

main outputs: 
Total energy need per end-use

DISTRICT and IN-HOUSE HEATING share

objective: The submodule aims at modeling the energy need split for decentralized and centralized (district) heating.

main inputs: 
energy need (energy-need[kWh/year]), 
x district heating share (district-heating-share[%])
x district heating coverage (district-heating-coverage)

main outputs: 
energy need district (energy-need-district_*[kWh/year]),
energy demand decentralized (energy-need-decentral_*[kWh/year]),

Final energy demand for DECENTRAL heating in residential and non-residential buildings

objective: The submodule aims at modeling the final energy demand for the different building types over time.

main inputs: 
energy need (energy-need[kWh/year]), 
heating and cooling technology and fuel mix in year x (heatcool-technology-fuel_.*[%])
heating and cooling technology efficiency [%]

main outputs: 
final energy demand (energy_*[kWh/year])

GHG EMISSIONS emitted each year

objective: The submodule calculates the greenhouse gas emissions from fuel combustion for heating in buildings

main inputs: 
bld_residential-energy-demand_ per fuel type [TWh],
co2factor_ per fuel type [gCO2/kWh]

main outputs: 
bld_residential-CO2emissions_  fuel type  [Mt]
Added to split energy need for sfh and mfh. This granularity wasn't available in EUCalc data

Floor area calculation for building types
in residential and non-residential buildings
 
objective: The submodule aims at calculating the floor area for the the different building types.
 
main inputs: 
total residential floor area in each year (floor-area[m²]),
building mix for residential and non-residential subsector [%]
floor area heated and cooled from lifestyle [m²]

 
main outputs: 
residential floor area in each year in total (floor-area_residential[m²])
residential floor area in each year for each buidling type (floor-area_residential_*[m²])
non-residential floor area in each year in total (floor-area_non-residential[m²])
non-residential floor area in each year for each buidling type (floor-area_non-residential_*[m²])

Select Energy-needs per unit of activity
for each type of end-use

OK ONLY FOR BELGIUM

Calibration - Energy
objective: The submodule aims at calibrating the final energy demand for the different energy uses in the household and the service sector, such as heating, appliances, lighting and cooking.

main inputs: 
energy balance from JRC IDEES

main outputs: 
calibration factor

Calibration - CO2 emissions

objective: The submodule aims at calibrating the CO2 emissions of the sector
